title: Teenage pregnancies in England and Wales resulting in maternities 2004 to 2017
yAxis: Number of pregnancies resulting in maternity
summary: This is a line chart with an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Number of pregnancies resulting in maternity, containing a total of 14 data points.
In general Number of pregnancies resulting in maternity has fallen over the Year.
Number of pregnancies resulting in maternity is roughly constant from 2004 to 2008, and finally slightly decreasing from 2008 to 2017.
The steepest decrease occurs in between the Year 2011 and 2012.
The highest Number of pregnancies resulting in maternity, of value 61111.0 was reached at Year 2005
Minimum Number of pregnancies resulting in maternity about 28092.0 was reached at Year 2017
